In large nonstick pot, cook bacon until crisp, Remove to paper towels, crumble, set aside, In same pot coated with nonstick cooking spray, saut√© mushrooms, garlic, and onion until tender about 7 minutes, Add thyme, broth, bay leaf, carrots, sweet potatoes and barley, Bring to boil, reduce heat, cover, and cook 25 minutes or until barley and vegetables are tender. Season to taste, remove bay leaf. If too thick, add more broth. To serve, sprinkle with crumbled bacon.